Method: Array.prototype.map(callbackFn, thisArg?) -> Array
Definition: Returns a new array with the results of calling callbackFn on every existing element in the calling array; does not mutate the original array. callbackFn is invoked with three arguments (currentValue, index, array). The length of the result equals the length of the original array; holes remain holes if not visited.

